President Cyril Ramaphosa will lead the call for a National Day of Prayer through a televised broadcast on Tuesday night. The address is expected to commence at 19h30. PRETORIA - President Cyril Ramaphosa will lead the call for a National Day of Prayer through a televised broadcast on Tuesday night. The address is expected to commence at 19h30. The Presidency says during the address Ramaphosa is also expected to provide an update on provisions for the religious sector following a meeting of the National Coronavirus Command Council. READ: Ramaphosa handled COVID-19 better than Johnson: Lord Peter Hain The Presidency further stated that the NCC considered the inputs made by the sector in recent consultations with interfaith leaders. Under the current lockdown regulations, places of religious worship remain closed. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.